Section 1: Q&A; Pairs

Example 1.1

User

What is batch normalization?
AI Response

Batch normalization normalizes layer inputs to have zero mean and unit variance, stabilizing training,
reducing initialization sensitivity, and acting as a mild regularizer.

Example 1.2

User

What is GPT?
AI Response

GPT (Generative Pre-trained Transformer) is an autoregressive language model trained to predict the next
token. GPT-3 and GPT-4 are large-scale versions capable of diverse language tasks.

Example 1.3

User

What is a neural network?
AI Response

A neural network is a series of algorithms modeled after the human brain, consisting of input, hidden, and
output layers, with weights adjusted during training to minimize prediction error.

Example 1.4

User

What is reinforcement learning?
AI Response

Reinforcement learning trains an agent to make decisions by interacting with an environment and receiving
rewards or penalties, aiming to maximize cumulative reward over time.

Example 1.5

User

What is fine-tuning?
AI Response

Fine-tuning updates a pre-trained model's weights on a smaller, task-specific dataset. It is more efficient than
training from scratch and achieves strong performance with limited data.

Example 1.6

User

What is a GAN?
AI Response

A Generative Adversarial Network pits a generator (creates fake data) against a discriminator (identifies
fakes), training each other until the generator produces realistic data.

Example 1.7

User

What is a loss function?
AI Response



A loss function quantifies the difference between a model's predictions and the actual targets. Examples
include Mean Squared Error for regression and Cross-Entropy Loss for classification.

Example 1.8

User

What is the ROC curve?
AI Response

The ROC curve plots true positive rate vs false positive rate at various thresholds. AUC (Area Under Curve)
summarizes performance—a perfect model has AUC = 1.0.

Example 1.9

User

What is tokenization in NLP?
AI Response

Tokenization splits text into smaller units (tokens) such as words, subwords, or characters. Subword
tokenization (BPE, WordPiece) balances vocabulary size with handling of rare words.

Example 1.10

User

What is data augmentation?
AI Response

Data augmentation artificially increases training data by applying transformations like rotation, cropping, and
flipping to existing samples, improving model generalization.



